            <div class="tip-card">
                <h3 class="tip-title">📋 Interview Structure (45-60 min)</h3>
                <div class="tip-content">
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>5 min:</strong> Clarify requirements & gather constraints</li>
                        <li><strong>5 min:</strong> High-level architecture & components</li>
                        <li><strong>10 min:</strong> Deep dive into core components</li>
                        <li><strong>10 min:</strong> Database schema & data flow</li>
                        <li><strong>10 min:</strong> Scalability & bottlenecks</li>
                        <li><strong>5 min:</strong> Tradeoffs & monitoring</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-card">
                <h3 class="tip-title">✅ Communication Best Practices</h3>
                <div class="tip-content">
                    <ul>
                        <li>Think out loud - show your reasoning</li>
                        <li>Start broad, then drill down</li>
                        <li>Discuss tradeoffs explicitly</li>
                        <li>Use numbers: QPS, storage, bandwidth</li>
                        <li>Ask for feedback: "Does this approach work?"</li>
                        <li>Don't jump to solutions immediately</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-card">
                <h3 class="tip-title">⚠️ Common Mistakes to Avoid</h3>
                <div class="tip-content">
                    <ul>
                        <li>Jumping into code without understanding</li>
                        <li>Over-engineering or under-engineering</li>
                        <li>Ignoring non-functional requirements</li>
                        <li>Not discussing tradeoffs</li>
                        <li>Skipping capacity estimation</li>
                        <li>Using buzzwords without understanding</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

